label: A3B_oP4_25_abc_d-001
title: Dyscrasite (Ag$_{3.15}$Sb$_{0.85}$) Structure
comments:
We have reordered the Wyckoff positions of this structure to match the AFLOW standard.  What (Scott, 1976) designated as the Sb (1a) site is now (1d).  That site is actually 85\% antimony and 15\% silver. 
 Space group $Pmm2$ \#25 allows an arbitary choice of the origin of the $z$-axis.  We set $z_{1} = 0$ for the (1a) site.
